s-trial-2020-national-league-421448|title=Badly Needed New Camogie Rules To Be Trialled In 2020 National League|first=P. J.|last=Browne|website=Balls.ie}}</ref>\n\nThe league was originally schedule to end in April 2020, but public health measures introduced to combat the spread of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] caused the final stages to be delayed, with potential for them to be shortened or cancelled altogether.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.clareecho.ie/u21-championship-delayed-clare-cup-deferred/|title=U21 championship delayed with Clare Cup start deferred|date=March 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://galwaybayfm.ie/sports/sporting-events-postponed-due-to-coronavirus-scare/|title=Sporting Events Postponed Due to Coronavirus Scare|first=Sport|last=GBFM|date=March 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/a-comprehensive-guide-as-irish-and-global-sport-shuts-down-in-effort-to-contain-spread-of-covid-19-39039369.html|title=Coronavirus: A comprehensive guide as Irish and global sport shuts down in effort to contain spread of Covid-19|website=independent}}</ref>\n\n==Format==\n===League structure===\nThe 2020 National Camogie League consists of three divisions: 9 in Division 1, 14 in Division 2 and 4 in Division 3; division 1 is divided into two groups and Division 2 is divided into three groups. Each team plays every other team in its group once. 3 points are awarded for a win and 1 for a draw.\n\nIf two teams are level on points, the tie-break is:\n* winners of the head-to-head game are ranked ahead\n* if the head-to-head match was a draw, ranking is determined by the points difference (i.e. total scored minus total conceded in all games)\n* if the points difference is equal, ranking is determined by the total scored\n\nIf three or more teams are level on league points, rankings are determined solely by points difference.\n\n===Finals ===\nThe winners of each group in Division 1 contest the National Camogie League final.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wearedublin.com/camogie/dublin-seniors-start-the-2020-national-camogie-league-against-galway/|title=Dublin Seniors Start The 2020 National Camogie League Against Galway|first=Nigel|last=McCarthy|date=December 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn Division 2, the three group winners and runners-up contest the quarter-finals; the three quarter-final winners then play a semi-final and final.\n\nThe top two teams in Division 3 contest the Division 3 final.\n\n==Fixtures and results==\n\n===Division 1===\n====Group 1====\n\n{| style=border-collapse:collapse border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=5\n|- align=center bgcolor=#efefef\n!Team\n!Pld\n!W\n!D\n!L\n!Diff\n!Pts\n!Notes\n\n|- align=center style=\"background:#BBEBFF\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Colours of Kilkenny.svg|20px|border]] [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]]\n||0||0 ||0 ||0 ||0|| '''0''' ||rowspan=1|Advance to NCL final\n|- align=center style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Colours of Cork.svg|20px|border]] [[Cork GAA|Cork]]\n||0||0 ||0 ||0 ||0|| '''0'''||rowspan=3|\n|- align=center style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Colours of Waterford.svg|20px|border]] [[Waterford GAA|Waterford]]\n||0||0 ||0 ||0 ||0|| '''0'''\n|- align=center style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Colours of Clare.svg|20px|border]] [[Clare GAA|Clare]]\n||0||0 ||0 ||0 ||0|| '''0'''\n|- align=center style=\"background:#FFCCCC;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Colours of Offaly.svg|20px|border]] [[Offaly GAA|Offaly]]\n||0||0 ||0 ||0 ||0|| '''0'''||Relegation playoff\n|}\n\n====Group 2====\n\n{| style=border-collapse:collapse border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=5\n|- align=center bgcolor=#efefef\n!Team\n!Pld\n!W\n!D\n!L\n!Diff\n!Pts\n!Notes\n\n|- align=center style=\"background:#BBEBFF\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Colours of Tipperary.svg|20px|border]] [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n||3 ||3 ||0 ||0 ||+22|| '''9'''||rowspan=1|Advance to NCL final\n|- align=center style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Colours of Galway.svg|20px|border]] [[Galway GAA|Galway]]\n||3||2 ||0 ||1 ||+6|| '''6''' ||rowspan=2|\n|- align=center style=\"background:#FFFFFF;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[File:Colours of Limerick.svg|20px|border]] [[Limerick GAA|Limerick]]\n||3||1 ||0 ||2 || \u201316|| '''3'''  \n|- align=center style=\"background:#FFCCCC;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[File:Colours of Dublin.svg|20px|border]] [[Dublin GAA|Dublin]]\n||3||0 ||0 ||3 || \u201312|| '''0''' ||Relegation playoff\n|}\n\n====Relegation playoff====\n{{Infobox GAA match\n|date = TBA\n|round = Relegation playoff\n|time = \n|team1 =  \n|score =   \n|team2 = [[Dublin GAA|Dublin]]\n|goals1 =\n|goals2=\n|stadium =  \n|attendance=\n|report= \n|referee =\n|stack = yes\n}}\n\n====Final====\n{{Infobox GAA match\n|date =TBA\n|round = Final\n|time = \n|team1 =  \n|score =   \n|team2 = [[Tipperary GAA|Tipperary]]\n|goals1 =\n|goals2=\n|stadium =  \n|attendance=\n|report= \n|referee =\n|stack = yes\n}}\n\n===Division 2===\n====Finals====\n\n===Division 3===\n====Final====\n{{Infobox GAA match\n|date =TBA\n|round = Final\n|time = \n|team1 =  \n|score =   \n|team2 = \n|goals1 =\n|goals2=\n|stadium =  \n|attendance=\n|report= \n|referee =\n|stack = yes\n}}\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n{{National Camogie League}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in camogie|League]]\n[[Category:National Camogie League seasons]]\n", "name_user": "Guliolopez", "label": "safe", "comment": "ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_National_Camogie_League"}
{"title_page": "2020 New Hampshire Wildcats football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| mode = football\n| year = 2020\n| team=New Hampshire Wildcats\n| image= UNH Wildcats.png\n| image_size= 150\n| conference= Colonial Athletic Association\n| division= \n| short_conf= CAA\n| STATSRank = \n| FCSCoachRank = \n| record = 0\u20130\n| conf_record = 0\u20130\n| head_coach= [[Sean McDonnell]]\n| hc_year = 21st\n| cooff_coach1 = Michael Ferzoco\n| cooc1_year = 2nd season as OC, 13th overall\n| cooff_coach2 = Alex Miller\n| cooc2_year = 2nd season as OC, 10th overall\n| def_coach=[[John Lyons (American football)|John Lyons]]\n| dc_year = 10th\n| off_scheme= \n| def_scheme=\n| stadium= [[Wildcat Stadium (University of New Hampshire)|Wildcat Stadium]]<br>(Capacity: 11,015)\n| champion = \n| bowl= \n| bowl_result = \n}}\n{{2020 Colonial Athletic Association football standings}}\nThe '''2020 New Hampshire Wildcats football team''' will represent the [[University of New Hampshire]] in the [[2020 NCAA Division I FCS football season]]. They will be led by 21st-year head coach [[Sean McDonnell]] following his leave of absence due to medical reasons during the 2019 season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bostonherald.com/2019/08/27/new-hampshire-football-coach-sean-mcdonnell-on-leave-for-health-reasons/ |title=New Hampshire football coach Sean McDonnell on leave for health reasons |first=John |last=Connolly |website=[[Boston Herald]] |url-access=limited |date=August 27, 2019 |accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref> The team will play their home games at [[Wildcat Stadium (University of New Hampshire)|Wildcat Stadium]] and are a member of the [[Colonial Athletic Association]] (CAA).\n\n==Previous season==\n{{main|2019 New Hampshire Wildcats football team}}\nThe Wildcats finished the [[2019 NCAA Division I FCS football season|2019 season]] 6\u20135, 5\u20133 in CAA play to finish tied for third place.\n\n==Schedule==\n{