Konosuke Takeshita]]\n|stip11   = Singles match\n|time11   = 24:21\n\n|match12  = [[Daisuke Sasaki]] defeated [[Danshoku Dino]] (c) by submission\n|stip12   = Singles match for the [[KO-D Openweight Championship]]\n|time12   = 32:10\n}}\n\n===Rumble rules match===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Order<ref name=Rumble>{{cite web | url = https://dramaticddt.wordpress.com/past-results/ddt-results-2018/ | title=DDT Results 2018 | accessdate=February 3, 2020 | work=Dramatic DDT}}</ref>\n! Wrestler\n! Order eliminated\n! By\n! Time\n|-style=\"background:gold\"\n| '''{{sort|01|1}}''' || '''{{sort|Shimatani|Nobuhiro Shimatani}}''' || {{sort|10|&mdash;}} || &mdash; || '''Winner'''\n|-\n| {{sort|02|2}} || {{sort|Imanari|Yumehito Imanari}} || {{sort|06|6}} || Gorgeous Matsuno || 10:59\n|-\n| {{sort|03|3}} || {{sort|Shota|Shota}} || {{sort|07|7}} || Gorgeous Matsuno || 10:59\n|-\n| {{sort|04|4}} || {{sortname||Tiger Mask V (self-proclaimed)|Tiger Mask (professional wrestling)}} || {{sort|01|1}} || Everyone || 6:43\n|-\n| {{sort|05|5}} || {{sort|Wolf|Michael Wolf}} || {{sort|03|3}} || Hoshitango || 8:34\n|-\n| {{sort|06|6}} || {{sort|Hitori|Gundan Hitori}} || {{sort|02|2}} || Hoshitango || 8:01\n|-\n| {{sort|07|7}} || {{sort|Monster|Monster Halloween}} || {{sort|04|4}} || Gorgeous Matsuno || 9:24\n|-\n| {{sort|08|8}} || {{sort|Ihashi|Gota Ihashi}} || {{sort|08|8}} || Nobuhiro Shimatani || 11:06\n|-\n| {{sort|09|9}} || {{sortname||Hoshitango|Hoshitango Imachi}} || {{sort|05|5}} || Gota Ihashi, Yumehito Imanari and Shota || 10:04\n|-\n| {{sort|10|10}} || {{sort|Matsuno|Gorgeous Matsuno}} || {{sort|09|9}} || Nobuhiro Shimatani || 13:26\n|}\n\n===Gauntlet tag team match===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n!Elimination\n!Wrestler\n!Team\n!Eliminated by\n!Elimination move\n!Time\n!Ref.\n|-\n|1\n|Mizuki Watase\n|Renegades\n|Mike Bailey\n|Pinned after an ''[[Professional wrestling aerial techniques#Shooting star knee drop|Ultima Weapon]]''\n|5:09\n|<ref name=DDT2018PL/>\n|-\n|2\n|Antonio Honda\n|Mike Bailey and Antonio Honda\n|Keisuke Okuda\n|[[Professional wrestling holds#Cross armbar|Cross armbreaker]]\n|8:28\n|<ref name=DDT2018PL/>\n|-\n|3\n|Tanomusaku Toba\n|Tanomusaku Toba and Keisuke Okuda\n|[[Michael Nakazawa]]\n|Pinned with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)|Japanese leg roll clutch]]\n|10:49\n|<ref name=DDT2018PL/>\n|-\n|4\n|[[Michael Nakazawa]]\n|Tomomitsu Matsunaga and [[Michael Nakazawa]]\n|[[Kudo (wrestler)|Kudo]]\n|Pinned after a [[Professional wrestling aerial techniques#Diving knee drop|Diving double knee drop]]\n|12:46\n|<ref name=DDT2018PL/>\n|-\n|5\n|Kota Umeda\n|Kazusada Higuchi and Kota Umeda\n|[[Masahiro Takanashi]]\n|Pinned after a ''[[Powerbomb#Sunset flip powerbomb|Taka Tonic]]''\n|18:52\n|<ref name=DDT2018PL/>\n|-\n!Winners:\n|colspan=\"6\" bgcolor=\"#f2f2f2\"|''Shuten-d\u014dji'' ([[Kudo (wrestler)|Kudo]] and [[Masahiro Takanashi]])\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.ddtpro.com/ The official DDT Pro-Wrestling website]\n*[http://www.prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/japan/lucha/ddt/peterpan.html#2018 Ry\u014dgoku Peter Pan 2018 at ProWrestlingHistory.com]\n\n{{Professional wrestling in Japan}}\n\n[[Category:DDT Peter Pan]]\n[[Category:2018 in professional wrestling]]\n[[Category:October 2018 events in Asia]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestling in Tokyo]]\n[[Category:2018 in Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Events in Tokyo]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 DDT Pro-Wrestling event}}\n{{Infobox Wrestling event\n|name=Ry\u014dgoku Peter Pan 2018: Fall Pro-Wrestling Cultural Festival\n|image=\n|caption=\n|promotion=[[DDT Pro-Wrestling]]\n|date={{dts|October 21, 2018}}<ref name=PeterPan2018CM />\n|venue=[[Ry\u014dgoku Kokugikan]]<ref name=PeterPan2018CM />\n|city=[[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]<ref name=PeterPan2018CM />\n|attendance=6,259<ref name=PeterPan2018CM />\n|event=[[DDT Peter Pan|Peter Pan]]\n|lastevent2=[[Ry\u014dgoku Peter Pan 2017|2017]]\n|nextevent2=[[Wrestle Peter Pan 2019|2019]]\n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''Ry\u014dgoku Peter Pan 2018: Fall Pro-Wrestling Cultural Festival'''|\u4e21\u56fd\u30d4\u30fc\u30bf\u30fc\u30d1\u30f32018\u301c\u79cb\u306e\u30d7\u30ed\u30ec\u30b9\u6587\u5316\u796d\u301c|Ry\u014dgoku P\u012bt\u0101 Pan 2018: aki no puroresu bunkasai}} was a [[professional wrestling]] event promoted by [[DDT Pro-Wrestling]] (DDT). The event took place on October 21, 2018, in [[Tokyo]] at the [[Ry\u014dgoku Kokugikan]]. The event, named after the traditional [[Cultural festival (Japan)|Japanese cultural festivals]], featured twelve matches, two of which were contested for [[Championship (professional wrestling)|championships]].<ref name=PeterPan2018CM>{{cite web | url = https://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=212537 | title = DDT Ryogoku Peter Pan 2018 ~ Fall Wrestling Culture Festival ~ | accessdate = February 3, 2020 | work = Cagematch.net}}</ref><ref name=DDT2018PL>{{cite web | url = http://www.purolove.com/misc/ddt/results/results18.php | title = DDT Pro-Wrestling Results: 2018 | language = German | accessdate = February 3, 2020 | work = Purolove.net}}</ref> The event aired on [[Fighting TV Samurai]] and was the first Peter Pan event to be held in fall.\n\n==Storylines==\nThe Ry\u014dgoku Peter Pan 2018 event featured twelve [[Professional wrestling match types|professional wrestling matches]] that involved different wrestlers from pre-existing scripted feuds and [[Narrative thread|storylines]]. Wrestlers portrayed [[Heel (professional wrestling)|villains]], [[Face (professional wrestling)|heroes]], or [[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#Tweener|less distinguishable characters]] in the scripted events that built tension and culminated in a wrestling match or series of matches.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://entertainment.howstuffworks.com/pro-wrestling.htm | title = How Pro Wrestling Works | last=Grabianowski | first=Ed | accessdate=September 13, 2014 | work=HowStuffWorks, Inc. | publisher=[[Discovery Communications]]}}</ref>\n\nBy winning the [[King of DDT Tournament#2018|King of DDT]] tournament on August 26, [[Daisuke Sasaki]] earned a title match in the main event against [[KO-D Openweight Championship|KO-D Openweight Champion]] [[Danshoku Dino]].\n\n==Event==\nFirst on the undercard was a ten-man [[Professional wrestling match types#Rumble rules battle royals|Rumble rules match]]. Amongst the participants was a fake [[Ikuhisa Minowa|Tiger Mask V]].\n\nThe second match of the undercard was Mira Shirakawa's first DDT match and featured six [[Tokyo Joshi Pro Wrestling]] talents.\n\nOn the main card, Disaster Box ([[Toru Owashi]], Kazuki Hirata and Yuki Ueno) challenged Damnation (Soma Takao, [[Tetsuya Endo (wrestler)|Tetsuya Endo]] and [[Mad Paulie]]) for the [[KO-D 6-Man Tag Team Championship]].\n\nNext was a six-team [[Gauntlet match]] in which two [[Tag Team Wrestling|tag teams]] begin the match and are replaced whenever one is eliminated (by pinfall or submission) until there is only one team left.\n\nNext was a tag team match dubbed \"Super Joshi Pro Wars 2018\" pitting Cassandra Miyagi and [[Meiko Satomura]] from [[Sendai Girls' Pro Wrestling]] against the team of [[Maki Itoh]] and Saki Akai.\n\nNext was a [[six-man tag team match]] between All Out (Akito, Shunma Katsumata and Yuki Iino) and #StrongHearts ([[T-Hawk (wrestler)|T-Hawk]], [[El Lindaman]] and Duan Yingnan).\n\nNext was an [[intergender tag team match]] between real life husband and wife [[Joey Ryan (wrestler)|Joey Ryan]] and [[Laura James (wrestler)|Laura James]], and real life [[Engagement|fianc\u00e9s]] [[Makoto Oishi]] and [[Misaki Ohata]] from [[Pro Wrestling Wave]]. The match was dubbed \"The World's Crazy Couple Battle\".\n\nNext was a match sponsored by Souken Holdings dubbed \"Eat Or Be Eaten!? Giant Special Single Match\" between Super Sasadango Machine and Andreza Giant Panda, a gigantic panda [[mascot]].\n\nNext was a [[Professional wrestling match types#Weapon-based variations|Weapon Rumble match]] dubbed \"The Difference In 27 Years Of Age! Bloodbath Between President (48) and Roster Member (21) &mdash; Final and Conclusive Weapon Rumble\" in which various weapons secretly chosen by the participants beforehand were being introduced one after another at regular intervals.\n\nNext was [[Shigehiro Irie]] send-off match. He teamed up with his Team Dream Futures partner [[Keisuke Ishii]] to take on the team of [[Harashima]] and [[Yukio Sakaguchi]].\n\nNext, [[Konosuke Takeshita]] faced off against [[Cima (wrestler)|Cima]].\n\nIn the main event, [[Daisuke Sasaki]] challenged [[Danshoku Dino]] for the [[KO-D Openweight Championship]]. Sasaki won the bout and was granted a 2,000,000 [[Japanese yen|yen]] prize by Good Com Asset, the sponsor of the match.\n\n==Results==\n{{Professional wrestling results table\n|future  = no\n|results = <ref name=PeterPan2018CM /><ref name=DDT2018PL /><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.ddtpro.com/results/1628 | script-title=ja:\u4e21\u56fd\u30d4\u30fc\u30bf\u30fc\u30d1\u30f32018\uff5e\u79cb\u306e\u30d7\u30ed\u30ec\u30b9\u6587\u5316\u796d\uff5e | date=October 21, 2018 | accessdate=February 3, 2020 | work=[[DDT Pro-Wrestling]] | language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|match1  = Nobuhiro Shimatani won by last eliminating Gorgeous Matsuno\n|stip1   = [[Professional wrestling match types#Rumble rules battle royals|Rumble rules match]]\n|time1   = 13:26\n|pre1    = yes\n\n|match2  = [[Yuka Sakazaki]], Mizuki and [[Shoko Nakajima]] defeated [[Miyu Yamashita]], Yuki Kamifuku and Mina Shirakawa\n|stip2   = [[Six-man tag team match|Six-woman tag team match]]\n|time2   = 9:08\n|pre2    = yes\n\n|match3  = Damnation (Soma Takao, [[Tetsuya Endo (wrestler)|Tetsuya Endo]] and [[Mad Paulie]]) (c) defeated Disaster Box ([[Toru Owashi]], Kazuki Hirata and Yuki Ueno)\n|stip3   = [[Six-man tag team match]] for the [[KO-D 6-Man Tag Team Championship]]\n|time3   = 11:21\n\n|match4  = ''Shuten-d\u014dji'' ([[Kudo (wrestler)|Kudo]] and [[Masahiro Takanashi]]) defeated Mike Bailey and Antonio Honda, Renegades (Mizuki Watase and [[Jason Kincaid|Jason \"The Gift\" Kincaid]]), Kazusada Higuchi and Kota Umeda, Tanomusaku Toba and Keisuke Okuda, and Tomomitsu Matsunaga and [[Michael Nakazawa]]\n|stip4   = [[Gauntlet match|Gauntlet tag team match]]\n|time4   = 18:52\n\n|match5  = [[Meiko Satomura]] and Cassandra Miyagi defeated Saki Akai and [[Maki Itoh]] by [[Submission (professional wrestling)|submission]]\n|stip5   = [[Tag team match]]\n|time5   = 11:07\n\n|match6  = #StrongHearts ([[T-Hawk (wrestler)|T-Hawk]], [[El Lindaman]] and Duan Yingnan) defeated All Out (Akito, Shunma Katsumata and Yuki Iino)\n|stip6   = Six-man tag team match\n|time6   = 11:20\n\n|match7  = [[Makoto Oishi]] and [[Misaki Ohata]] defeated [[Joey Ryan (wrestler)|Joey Ryan]] and [[Laura James (wrestler)|Laura James]]\n|stip7   = Tag team match\n|time7   = 6:45\n\n|match8  = Andreza Giant Panda defeated Super Sasadango Machine\n|stip8   = [[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time8   = 10:25\n\n|match9  = Mao defeated [[Sanshiro Takagi]]\n|stip9   = [[Professional wrestling match types#Weapon-based variations|Weapon Rumble]]\n|time9   = 24:05\n\n|match10  = Team Dream Futures ([[Shigehiro Irie]] and [[Keisuke Ishii]]) defeated [[Harashima]] and [[Yukio Sakaguchi]]\n|stip10   = Tag team match\n|time10   = 14:50\n\n|match11  = [[Cima (wrestler)|Cima]] defeated [[Konosuke Takeshita]]\n|stip11   = Singles match\n|time11   = 24:21\n\n|match12  = [[Daisuke Sasaki]] defeated [[Danshoku Dino]] (c) by submission\n|stip12   = Singles match for the [[KO-D Openweight Championship]]\n|time12   = 32:10\n}}\n\n===Rumble rules match===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Order<ref name=Rumble>{{cite web | url = https://dramaticddt.wordpress.com/past-results/ddt-results-2018/ | title=DDT Results 2018 | accessdate=February 3, 2020 | work=Dramatic DDT}}</ref>\n! Wrestler\n! Order eliminated\n! By\n! Time\n|-style=\"background:gold\"\n| '''{{sort|01|1}}''' || '''{{sort|Shimatani|Nobuhiro Shimatani}}''' || {{sort|10|&mdash;}} || &mdash; || '''Winner'''\n|-\n| {{sort|02|2}} || {{sort|Imanari|Yumehito Imanari}} || {{sort|06|6}} || Gorgeous Matsuno || 10:59\n|-\n| {{sort|03|3}} || {{sort|Shota|Shota}} || {{sort|07|7}} || Gorgeous Matsuno || 10:59\n|-\n| {{sort|04|4}} || {{sortname||Tiger Mask V (self-proclaimed)|Tiger Mask (professional wrestling)}} || {{sort|01|1}} || Everyone || 6:43\n|-\n| {{sort|05|5}} || {{sort|Wolf|Michael Wolf}} || {{sort|03|3}} || Hoshitango || 8:34\n|-\n| {{sort|06|6}} || {{sort|Hitori|Gundan Hitori}} || {{sort|02|2}} || Hoshitango || 8:01\n|-\n| {{sort|07|7}} || {{sort|Monster|Monster Halloween}} || {{sort|04|4}} || Gorgeous Matsuno || 9:24\n|-\n| {{sort|08|8}} || {{sort|Ihashi|Gota Ihashi}} || {{sort|08|8}} || Nobuhiro Shimatani || 11:06\n|-\n| {{sort|09|9}} || {{sortname||Hoshitango|Hoshitango Imachi}} || {{sort|05|5}} || Gota Ihashi, Yumehito Imanari and Shota || 10:04\n|-\n| {{sort|10|10}} || {{sort|Matsuno|Gorgeous Matsuno}} || {{sort|09|9}} || Nobuhiro Shimatani || 13:26\n|}\n\n===Gauntlet tag team match===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n!Elimination\n!Wrestler\n!Team\n!Eliminated by\n!Elimination move\n!Time\n!Ref.\n|-\n|1\n|Mizuki Watase\n|Renegades\n|Mike Bailey\n|Pinned after an ''[[Professional wrestling aerial techniques#Shooting star knee drop|Ultima Weapon]]''\n|5:09\n|<ref name=DDT2018PL/>\n|-\n|2\n|Antonio Honda\n|Mike Bailey and Antonio Honda\n|Keisuke Okuda\n|[[Professional wrestling holds#Cross armbar|Cross armbreaker]]\n|8:28\n|<ref name=DDT2018PL/>\n|-\n|3\n|Tanomusaku Toba\n|Tanomusaku Toba and Keisuke Okuda\n|[[Michael Nakazawa]]\n|Pinned with a [[Pin (professional wrestling)|Japanese leg roll clutch]]\n|10:49\n|<ref name=DDT2018PL/>\n|-\n|4\n|[[Michael Nakazawa]]\n|Tomomitsu Matsunaga and [[Michael Nakazawa]]\n|[[Kudo (wrestler)|Kudo]]\n|Pinned after a [[Professional wrestling aerial techniques#Diving knee drop|Diving double knee drop]]\n|12:46\n|<ref name=DDT2018PL/>\n|-\n|5\n|Kot